  "texts": [
    "This study introduces the foot in the door (FITD) attack, a novel adversarial strategy in the IPI setup illustrated in Figure 1.",
    "The FITD attack involves presenting an LLM-based agent with a small, harmless, yet deceptive request, prior to the malicious instruction.",
    "This initial request can take the form of a harmless request, such as calculating a simple math problem, which serves as a precursor to the subsequent malicious action.",
    "By exploiting the agent's access to external tools, the FITD attack leverages the agent's propensity to trust and follow instructions, thereby reducing its likelihood of re-evaluating later, more harmful actions.",
    "Our experimental results demonstrate that the Figure 1: Foot-in-the-door attack flow."
